Quick Rules for Shortest Path
| Graph Type             | Edge Weight     | Algorithm                 |
| ---------------------- | --------------- | ------------------------- |
| DAG                    | Any (neg/pos)   | Topo sort + relaxation    |
| Any                    | Non-negative    | Dijkstra                  |
| Any                    | Can be negative | Bellman-Ford              |
| Unweighted             | N/A             | BFS                       |
| Small graph, all-pairs | Any             | Floyd-Warshall (optional) |


Strategy for Interviews
Start with BFS / DFS basics → grid problems → islands, rotting oranges.
Master Topo sort / DAG problems → course schedule, alien dictionary.
Master Shortest path algorithms → BFS, Dijkstra, DAG shortest path, network delay time.
Practice Cycle detection in directed & undirected graphs.
Optional: understand Floyd-Warshall and Bellman-Ford conceptually.
